<h1>News</h1>

<a href="newsarchive.jsp">View The News Archive</a> 

	<h2>EQ Players In-Game Email</h2>
	
		
			<a href="&nbsp;">
		
		<img src="&nbsp;" border="0">
		
			</a>
		
		<br>
	
	<div align="left"> <p align="left">Now you can send in-game messages to other players even if they're not logged into the game! Here's how to use this new EverQuest feature: <br> </p> <table width="75%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="6"> <tr> <td><div align="left"><a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/content_images/eq_email/mail_ui.jpg"><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/content_images/eq_email/mail_ui_thumb.jpg" border="0"></a></div></td> <td><div align="right"><a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/content_images/eq_email/mail_ui2.jpg"><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/content_images/eq_email/mail_ui2_thumb.jpg" border="0"></a></div></td> </tr> </table> </div> <p>1) To open the Mail Window, either click on the Mail Icon (it's new!) or use Control-M.</p> <p>2) To send an e-mail, press the &quot;Compose&quot; button in the Mail Window. Enter the recipient's character name in the &quot;To&quot; field; then enter the &quot;Subject&quot; and type in the message. Press &quot;Send.&quot;</p> <p>3) To receive messages, click on an unread message header on the list in your Mail Window. You can also reply to the sender and forward the message to another player. </p> <p>4) There are also message management features where you can order, delete, or undelete messages. And you can even send a message to yourself. <br> </p> 

